Wolmido Island was once an island about 1 km away from the Qianhai Sea of Incheon, but it was gradually connected to the land during the construction of the road. Wolmido is named after the shape of the island in the shape of a half-moon tail. Wolmi Island is not far from Seoul, and the transportation is convenient. Tourists often come here on weekends. There are cafes, sashimi shops, restaurants, etc. on Wolmido Island. What a pleasure it is to enjoy the beautiful scenery of the West Sea and taste delicious food. There are more than 50 sashimi shops on the island, carefully making delicious seafood for tourists. In addition, the 1,200-meter-long Cultural Street extends from graffiti pillars, encounter places, art venues, and performance venues all the way. There are performances here as soon as they come, and street painters also improvise paintings for tourists. A must-see on Wolmi Island is the amusement park. Although not comparable to other large-scale theme parks, the amusement park is famous for Apollodisco and pirate ships. Thrilling pirate ships attract tourists from all over the country, and Apollodisco is a lot of fun even just looking around. From Wolmi Island, you can also take a cruise around the beautiful scenery at any time. The cool sea breeze, the clear waters of the West Sea, and the seagulls hovering in the sky are all intoxicating.

Seoul Amusement Park is a large theme amusement park in South Korea, located near Cheonggyesan Mountain in Mogye-dong, Gwacheon City, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea. Covers an area of 100,000 square meters. There are not only the World Plaza, which shows the styles of various countries in the world, but also the Sanqianli Dongshan Mountain, which expresses the traditional beauty of Korea. There are also two other exhibition areas with the theme of the country of westward movement and the country of fantasy.

description: Suwon Hwaseong is the 22nd Dynasty Dynasty King Jeongjo, in order to mourn his father, the second son of Youngjo. Although he was canonized as the heir, he was excluded from the faction struggle and failed to ascend to the throne. He ended his life in the rice cabinet. He moved the remains of his father from Baebongsan Mountain in Yangju to be buried here, and moved the eup city near Hwasan Mountain to its current location at the foot of Paldal Mountain in Suwon, and built Suwon Hwaseong Fortress.
